Case 1:20-cr-00330-PAE Document 765 Filed 08/10/22 Page 86 of 95 2824 LCIAMAX2ps
1 MR. EVERDELL: Count Two, "enticement of an individual under the age of 17." And then we would propose "(Jane only)," to add the word "only," your Honor.
2
3 THE COURT: So adding, after "an individual," "under the age of 17," adding in the parentheses, after the word "Jane," "only."
4
5 MR. EVERDELL: Correct.
6
7 THE COURT: OK.
8
9 MR. EVERDELL: Count Three, to transport and then take out the word "a minor," this would be, I guess, "individuals under the age of 17."
10
11 MR. ROHRBACH: Agreed, your Honor.
12
13 THE COURT: OK. I will make that change to "individuals under the age of 17," taking out "a minor."
14
15 MR. EVERDELL: And then Count Four, "transportation of an individual," adding "under the age of 17" and adding the word "only" after "Jane."
16
17 THE COURT: OK.
18
19 MR. ROHRBACH: That's fine, your Honor.
20
21 THE COURT: All right. Make that change, adding "under the age of 17" and then adding "only" after the word "Jane."
22
23 MR. EVERDELL: Let's just skip over Count Five for a second. Count Six.
24
25 THE COURT: "Only."
    SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300
